description:
English graphic novel translation.

On its maiden voyage, off the coast of Syria, the crew of the new super-submarine, USS Nebraska, receives a mysterious distress signal. At the bottom of the ocean cracks begin to show, and with a pair of maverick reporters on board, and a crew slowly losing their minds, they encounter an insidious and sinister force more terrifying they could possibly imagine. This bestselling Lovecraftian horror thriller "Sanctum" has been completely remastered by adding new characters, extra background storylines and unexpected plot twists. If "Sanctum" is the movie, then "Sanctum Redux" is the TV series. Bigger, deeper, darker, deadlier.
name: Sanctum Redux

description:
English digital edition.

A group of retired Lucha Libre masked heroes hope for well-deserved peace and quiet on a small Polynesian island. Unbeknownst to them, their greatest adventures have yet to come ! Philoloco, Doctor Sumo, Polynome Z and Cerebrex are four retired Luchadores known as The Tikitis. They thought life would be easy living on a savage island. Boy, were they wrong ! Amidst dealing with growing old, the foursome accidentally find themselves in the most wild of habitats, where world-threatening evildoers regularly create turmoil. It's hard to call retired life on a tropical island paradise when you have to deal with Voodoo zombies, brain-swapping mad scientists, a cyclops and, worst of all, a visit from Philoloco's overbearing mother !
name: The Tikitis

description:
When two college students watch a cursed film reel starring the forgotten 1930's cartoon character Mr. Scootles, they unknowingly set off a chain of events that could lead to Hell on Earth. Featuring a cast that includes a beautiful skirt-wearing demon, a bloodthirsty professor, a warrior angel, Judas, and the Devil herself. Mr. Scootles is a mystery-filled tale that is a tribute to the art of animation and its creators.

This is the collected TPB. For the digital version, see Mr. Scootles
name: Mr. Scootles

description:
English translation of the Japanese manga Toaru Majutsu no Kinsho Mokuroku (とある魔術の禁書目録).

A Certain Magical Index has enjoyed an astounding number of adaptations and spin-offs in manga format as well as animation, video games and a wide variety of collector merchandise. Currently there are four ongoing manga adaptations and manga spin-offs being published in Japan!

Two anime adaptations of the main series have aired in Japan between 2008-2010, with another two anime adaptations of its manga spin-off series, A Certain Scientific Railgun – which has become its own massively popular franchise – airing from 2009-2010, and in 2013. A Certain Magical Index the Movie was also released in 2013, showing that fan support of the series holds strong! Funimation has licensed all the anime adaptations for North American distribution.
name: A Certain Magical Index
